    "notes": "Likely issued from 1970-1973 as front cover has \"Special Buy!\"\n\nLive Album recorded at Mothers Birmingham & Manchester College of Commerce, June 1969\nSecond studio album LP features multi-part experimental pieces each written by an individual band member.\n\n6th pressing with SKBB-388 on both sleeve and Harvest label;\nFront sleeve: \"Gigi\" album cover leaning against wall is whited out;\nText around bottom half edge of label starts at 10:00 position and states:\n\"Mfd. by Capitol Records, Inc., a subsidiary of Capitol Industries-EMI, Inc., U.S.A. - Capitol Marca Reg. - All rights reserved. Unauthorized duplication is a violation of applicable laws.\"\nNext issue (7th pressing) split this text onto top and bottom half of label.\n\nMatrix inscriptions are etched, except for \"MASTERED BY CAPITOL\" which is stamped.\nSome parts of STBB in matrix inscriptions have T and K superimposed.",
